HEADWORD: autolysis
<hw>autolysis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>lysis of cells or
tissues due to enzymatic activity from within the cell, as contrasted
with externally induced lysis.</def> <note>Autolysis occurs to tissues
of higher animals when they are detached from the organism.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>autolytic</ent>⟦br⟧
